Whispers in Hollywood point toward a God of War adaptation, with Dwayne Johnson rumored to take on the role of Kratos. The idea of Johnson embodying the Spartan warrior has gained traction among fans who imagine his physicality translating into the brutal world of Greek mythology.

Reports suggest the story could follow the early years of Kratos, charting his rise from a Spartan general to the Ghost of Sparta. A focus on vengeance, loss, and redemption could provide the dramatic weight needed for a cinematic retelling.

The adaptation has been a longtime dream project for many studios, and Johnson’s involvement would add star power and global appeal to the potential franchise.

JUJUTSU KAISEN Season 3 is coming exclusively to Crunchyroll January 2026! Watch JUJUTSU KAISEN Crunchyroll! https://got.cr/cc-jjkpv

Yuji Itadori is a boy with tremendous physical strength, though he lives a completely ordinary high school life. One day, to save a classmate who has been attacked by curses, he eats the finger of Ryomen Sukuna, taking the curse into his own soul. From then on, he shares one body with Ryomen Sukuna. Guided by the most powerful of sorcerers, Satoru Gojo, Itadori is admitted to Tokyo Jujutsu High School, an organization that fights the curses... and thus begins the heroic tale of a boy who became a curse to exorcise a curse, a life from which he could never turn back.

Crunchyroll brings you the latest clips, openings, full episodes, and more from your favorite anime!

snippet.title: Marvel Animation's Marvel Zombies - Official Trailer #2 (2025) Elizabeth Olsen, Paul Rudd
snippet.description:
Check out the Trailer #2 for Marvel Animation’s Marvel Zombies, an animated horror installment to the Marvel Cinematic Universe distributed by Marvel Studios. This series re-contextualizes the Marvel Universe as Earth's mightiest heroes go head-to-head against a zombie outbreak, turning even the strongest of them into undead nightmares. Marvel Animation’s Marvel Zombies will be a four-part event on September 24, streaming exclusively on Disney+.

After the Avengers are overtaken by a zombie plague, a desperate group of survivors discover the key to bringing an end to the super-powered undead, racing across a dystopian landscape and risking life and limb to save their world. 
 
Marvel Zombies stars Elizabeth Olsen, Paul Rudd, Florence Pugh, David Harbour, Tessa Thompson, Simu Liu, Awkwafina, Hailee Steinfeld, Wyatt Russell, Randall Park, Iman Vellani, Dominique Thorne, and more. The series is executive produced by Kevin Feige, Louis D’Esposito, Brad Winderbaum, Dana Vasquez-Eberhardt, Bryan Andrews, and Zeb Wells, and is produced by Danielle Costa, Carrie Wassenaar. 

Marvel Animation’s Marvel Zombies will be a four-part event on September 24, streaming exclusively on Disney+.

#MarvelZombies #Marvel #IGN
